<taxonomicName id="4759B1E7237C8F82D8EB002BA6B55415" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33833" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole littoralis Cole" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole littoralis Cole" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis">littoralis</taxonomicName>
foveate, and in 
<taxonomicName id="DED644685C361F823F21611EA3D47909" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33868" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole micula Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole micula Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micula">micula</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6293A76E5829BD7D31488E8C771B272D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142583" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole soritis Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole soritis Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soritis">soritis</taxonomicName>
carinulate); postpetiole from above diamond-shaped, trapezoidal, or spinose. Minor: eye medium-sized to large.
</paragraph>
